
If you use a hierarchical module system, you can add additional toolchains manually.


Step 1: create new module data base
===================================

Suppose you want to create a database of modules under toolchain foss/2025

cd $DRONA_ENV_DIR/configuration
module load foss/2025
./generate_modules_db.py -b
mv modules.sqlite3 ../modules/modules-foss-2025.sqlite


Step 2: Add toolchain to module element in schema
=================================================

cd ../schemas
vi create.schema.json

in Module element, under toolchains, add :

      {
        "label": "foss/2025",
        "value": "modules-foss-2025"
      }


Since this is a JSON formatted file, don't forget to add a comma between the old label/value element and the newly added label/value element.

The newlyy  added toolchain will be available in the dropdown. You can add as many toolchains as needed. 
